The paper proposes a novel technique for integrating model-free and model-based approaches in reinforcement learning to achieve high performance with low sample complexity. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV). Given the focus on reinforcement learning and sample efficiency, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely categories, followed by cs.RO and cs.SY, which are relevant to robotics and control applications. cs.CV is less likely but still possible, as computer vision is often used in reinforcement learning applications.
